name

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Mono' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Mono Thin'.

IBM Plex Mono Thin Regular (IBMPlexMono-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexMono-Thin', Everything looks good.

IBM Plex Mono Thin Regular (IBMPlexMono-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Mono' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Mono Thin'.

NID 16 'IBM Plex Mono' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Mono Thin' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

IBM Plex Mono ExtraLight Regular (IBMPlexMono-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Mono' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Mono ExtraLight'.

Pass

IBM Plex Mono ExtraLight Regular (IBMPlexMono-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexMono-ExtraLight', Everything looks good.

Pass

IBM Plex Mono ExtraLight Regular (IBMPlexMono-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Mono' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Mono ExtraLight'.

Pass

Mac NID 6

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexMono-ExtraLightItalic', Everything looks good.

IBM Plex Mono ExtraLight Italic (IBMPlexMono-ExtraLightItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Mono' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Mono ExtraLight' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

IBM Plex Mono ExtraLight Italic (IBMPlexMono-ExtraLightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Mono' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Mono ExtraLight' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

IBM Plex Mono Light Italic (IBMPlexMono-LightItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexMono-LightItalic', Everything looks good.

IBM Plex Mono Light Italic (IBMPlexMono-LightItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Mono' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Mono Light' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

IBM Plex Mono Light Italic (IBMPlexMono-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexMono-LightItalic', Everything looks good.

IBM Plex Mono Light Italic (IBMPlexMono-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Mono' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Mono Light' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

IBM Plex Mono Italic (IBMPlexMono-Italic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexMono-Italic', Everything looks good.

, most common Monotype license test is:
This font software is the property of Monotype Imaging Inc., or one of its affiliated entities (collectively, Monotype) and its use by you is covered under the terms of a license agreement. You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. IBM Plex Mono Medium Italic (IBMPlexMono-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Mono' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Mono Medium' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

This font software is the property of Monotype Imaging Inc., or one of its affiliated entities (collectively, Monotype) and its use by you is covered under the terms of a license agreement. You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. You can learn more about Monotype by clicking here: www.monotype.com.

IBM Plex Mono Medium Italic (IBMPlexMono-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Mono' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Mono Medium' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

IBM Plex Mono SemiBold Italic (IBMPlexMono-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexMono-SemiBoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

IBM Plex Mono SemiBold Italic (IBMPlexMono-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Mono' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Mono SemiBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

IBM Plex Mono SemiBold Italic (IBMPlexMono-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexMono-SemiBoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

IBM Plex Mono SemiBold Italic (IBMPlexMono-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Mono' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Mono SemiBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

IBM Plex Mono Bold (IBMPlexMono-Bold.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexMono-Bold', Everything looks good.

IBM Plex Mono Bold Italic (IBMPlexMono-BoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexMono-BoldItalic', Everything looks good.
